  "Step 1: Determine the inverse function \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) for the given piecewise function \\( f(x) \\).\n\nFor \\( x < 4 \\), we have \\( f(x) = x - 2 \\). The inverse of this part is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y + 2 \\quad \\text{for} \\quad y < 2. \\]\n\nFor \\( x \\ge 4 \\), we have \\( f(x) = \\sqrt{x} \\). The inverse of this part is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y^2 \\quad \\text{for} \\quad y \\ge 2. \\]\n\nStep 2: Evaluate \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) for each integer \\( y \\) from \\(-5\\) to \\(5\\).\n\n- For \\( y = -5, -4, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1 \\), we use \\( f^{-1}(y) = y + 2 \\):\n  \\[ f^{-1}(-5) = -5 + 2 = -3, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(-4) = -4 + 2 = -2, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(-3) = -3 + 2 = -1, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(-2) = -2 + 2 = 0, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(-1) = -1 + 2 = 1, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(0) = 0 + 2 = 2, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(1) = 1 + 2 = 3. \\]\n\n- For \\( y = 2, 3, 4, 5 \\), we use \\( f^{-1}(y) = y^2 \\):\n  \\[ f^{-1}(2) = 2^2 = 4, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(3) = 3^2 = 9, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(4) = 4^2 = 16, \\]\n  \\[ f^{-1}(5) = 5^2 = 25. \\]\n\nStep 3: Sum the values of \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) from \\( y = -5 \\) to \\( y = 5 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-5) + f^{-1}(-4) + f^{-1}(-3) + f^{-1}(-2) + f^{-1}(-1) + f^{-1}(0) + f^{-1}(1) + f^{-1}(2) + f^{-1}(3) + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5) = -3 + (-2) + (-1) + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25. \\]\n\nStep 4: Simplify the sum:\n\\[ -3 - 2 - 1 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 = (-3 + 3) + (-2 + 2) + (-1 + 1) + 0 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 = 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 = 54. \\]\n\nThe final answer is:\n\\[ \\boxed{54}. \\]",
  "Step 1: Determine the inverse function \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) for each piece of the piecewise function \\( f(x) \\).\n\nFor \\( x < 4 \\):\n\\[ f(x) = x - 2 \\]\nTo find the inverse, solve for \\( x \\) in terms of \\( y \\):\n\\[ y = x - 2 \\]\n\\[ x = y + 2 \\]\nThus, the inverse function for \\( x < 4 \\) is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y + 2 \\quad \\text{for} \\quad y < 2 \\]\n\nFor \\( x \\ge 4 \\):\n\\[ f(x) = \\sqrt{x} \\]\nTo find the inverse, solve for \\( x \\) in terms of \\( y \\):\n\\[ y = \\sqrt{x} \\]\n\\[ x = y^2 \\]\nThus, the inverse function for \\( x \\ge 4 \\) is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y^2 \\quad \\text{for} \\quad y \\ge 2 \\]\n\nStep 2: Evaluate \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) for each integer \\( y \\) from \\(-5\\) to \\( 5 \\).\n\nFor \\( y = -5 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-5) = -5 + 2 = -3 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = -4 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-4) = -4 + 2 = -2 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = -3 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-3) = -3 + 2 = -1 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = -2 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-2) = -2 + 2 = 0 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = -1 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-1) = -1 + 2 = 1 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 0 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(0) = 0 + 2 = 2 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 1 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(1) = 1 + 2 = 3 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 2 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(2) = 2^2 = 4 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 3 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(3) = 3^2 = 9 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 4 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(4) = 4^2 = 16 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 5 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(5) = 5^2 = 25 \\]\n\nStep 3: Sum the values of \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) from \\( y = -5 \\) to \\( y = 5 \\).\n\n\\[\nf^{-1}(-5) + f^{-1}(-4) + f^{-1}(-3) + f^{-1}(-2) + f^{-1}(-1) + f^{-1}(0) + f^{-1}(1) + f^{-1}(2) + f^{-1}(3) + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -3 + (-2) + (-1) + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25\n\\]\n\nStep 4: Calculate the sum.\n\n\\[\n-3 - 2 - 1 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25\n\\]\n\nGrouping the terms for easier calculation:\n\n\\[\n(-3 - 2 - 1) + (0 + 1 + 2 + 3) + (4 + 9 + 16 + 25)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -6 + 6 + 54\n\\]\n\\[\n= 0 + 54\n\\]\n\\[\n= 54\n\\]\n\nThus, the value of \\( f^{-1}(-5) + f^{-1}(-4) + \\dots + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5) \\) is \\(\\boxed{54}\\).",
  "Step 1: Determine the intervals for which the function \\( f(x) \\) is defined.\nFor \\( x < 4 \\), \\( f(x) = x - 2 \\).\nFor \\( x \\ge 4 \\), \\( f(x) = \\sqrt{x} \\).\n\nStep 2: Find the inverse functions for each interval.\nFor \\( x < 4 \\), \\( f(x) = x - 2 \\). Solving for \\( x \\) in terms of \\( y \\):\n\\[ y = x - 2 \\implies x = y + 2 \\]\nThus, the inverse function for \\( y < 2 \\) is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y + 2 \\]\n\nFor \\( x \\ge 4 \\), \\( f(x) = \\sqrt{x} \\). Solving for \\( x \\) in terms of \\( y \\):\n\\[ y = \\sqrt{x} \\implies x = y^2 \\]\nThus, the inverse function for \\( y \\ge 2 \\) is:\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y^2 \\]\n\nStep 3: Evaluate \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) for each integer \\( y \\) from \\(-5\\) to \\(5\\).\nFor \\( y = -5 \\) to \\( y = 1 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y + 2 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(-5) = -5 + 2 = -3 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(-4) = -4 + 2 = -2 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(-3) = -3 + 2 = -1 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(-2) = -2 + 2 = 0 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(-1) = -1 + 2 = 1 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(0) = 0 + 2 = 2 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(1) = 1 + 2 = 3 \\]\n\nFor \\( y = 2 \\) to \\( y = 5 \\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(y) = y^2 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(2) = 2^2 = 4 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(3) = 3^2 = 9 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(4) = 4^2 = 16 \\]\n\\[ f^{-1}(5) = 5^2 = 25 \\]\n\nStep 4: Sum the values of \\( f^{-1}(y) \\) from \\(-5\\) to \\(5\\):\n\\[ f^{-1}(-5) + f^{-4}(-4) + f^{-3}(-3) + f^{-2}(-2) + f^{-1}(-1) + f^{-1}(0) + f^{-1}(1) + f^{-1}(2) + f^{-1}(3) + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5) \\]\n\\[ = -3 + (-2) + (-1) + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 \\]\n\nStep 5: Calculate the sum:\n\\[ -3 - 2 - 1 + 0 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 \\]\n\\[ = (-3 - 2 - 1 + 1) + (0 + 2 + 3) + (4 + 9 + 16 + 25) \\]\n\\[ = -5 + 5 + 54 \\]\n\\[ = 54 \\]\n\nThus, the value of \\( f^{-1}(-5) + f^{-1}(-4) + \\dots + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5) \\) is \\(\\boxed{54}\\).",
  "Step 1: Determine the inverse function $f^{-1}(y)$ for each piece of the piecewise function $f(x)$.\n\nFor $x < 4$, we have $f(x) = x - 2$. To find $f^{-1}(y)$, solve $y = x - 2$ for $x$:\n\\[\nx = y + 2\n\\]\nThus, for $y < 2$, $f^{-1}(y) = y + 2$.\n\nFor $x \\ge 4$, we have $f(x) = \\sqrt{x}$. To find $f^{-1}(y)$, solve $y = \\sqrt{x}$ for $x$:\n\\[\nx = y^2\n\\]\nThus, for $y \\ge 2$, $f^{-1}(y) = y^2$.\n\nStep 2: Evaluate $f^{-1}(y)$ for each integer $y$ from $-5$ to $5$.\n\nFor $y = -5$ to $y = 1$ (since $1 < 2$):\n\\[\nf^{-1}(y) = y + 2\n\\]\n\\[\nf^{-1}(-5) = -3, \\quad f^{-1}(-4) = -2, \\quad f^{-1}(-3) = -1, \\quad f^{-1}(-2) = 0, \\quad f^{-1}(-1) = 1\n\\]\n\nFor $y = 2$ to $y = 5$ (since $2 \\le 2$ and $5 \\ge 2$):\n\\[\nf^{-1}(y) = y^2\n\\]\n\\[\nf^{-1}(2) = 4, \\quad f^{-1}(3) = 9, \\quad f^{-1}(4) = 16, \\quad f^{-1}(5) = 25\n\\]\n\nStep 3: Sum the values of $f^{-1}(y)$ from $y = -5$ to $y = 5$:\n\\[\nf^{-1}(-5) + f^{-1}(-4) + f^{-1}(-3) + f^{-1}(-2) + f^{-1}(-1) + f^{-1}(0) + f^{-1}(1) + f^{-1}(2) + f^{-1}(3) + f^{-1}(4) + f^{-1}(5)\n\\]\n\\[\n= (-3) + (-2) + (-1) + 0 + 1 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25\n\\]\n\nStep 4: Calculate the sum:\n\\[\n-3 - 2 - 1 + 0 + 1 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25\n\\]\n\\[\n= (-3 - 2 - 1) + (0) + (1 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -6 + (1 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -6 + 55\n\\]\n\\[\n= 49\n\\]\n\nThus, the value is \\(\\boxed{49}\\)."
